      "assets": [],
      "author": "AyWutiansui",
      "description": "## Bug Fix\n- **Focus stealing**: Typing that causes the embedded OneNote window to reposition (e.g., pressing Enter shifts the embed down) no longer steals input focus from the Obsidian editor.\n\n### Technical changes\n- Narrowed MutationObserver to exclude `characterData` changes and added RAF debouncing — prevents keystrokes from triggering expensive reposition cycles\n- Added `WS_EX_NOACTIVATE` to reparented OneNote child window — prevents the embedded window from stealing input focus\n- Replaced `HWND_TOP` with `SWP_NOZORDER` on subsequent repositions — avoids activating the embedded window during scroll/typing\n- Added throttled focus watchdog (500ms cooldown) in reposition callback — restores editor focus if lost",
      "downloadCount": 0,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "v1.3.1 — Fix focus stealing on embed reposition",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2026-06-18T11:36:51Z",
      "tag": "v1.3.1"
